The paper deals with image segmentation, which is a computer vision task, and proposes a new model for learning inter-domain mappings from unpaired data. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques and the need for flexible mappings, which suggests that it could also be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper examines the model's performance on several image datasets, which could make it relevant to cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
